[[File:RNB 0457.jpg|thumb|Quarry-faced stone on the [[Inbal Jerusalem Hotel]]]]
'''Quarry-faced stone''' is stone with a rough, unpolished surface, straight from the [[quarry]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Straight|first=Susan|title=Rock Walls and Stone Sunbursts: The Quarry-Faced Homes of Southern California's Past|url=http://www.kcet.org/updaily/socal_focus/commentary/notes-of-a-native-daughter/rock-walls-and-stone-sunbursts-the-quarry-faced-homes-of-southern-californias-past.html|publisher=KCETLink|accessdate=29 March 2014|date=26 July 2012}}</ref>  Many residential and public buildings in [[Jerusalem]], [[Israel]] are built from quarry-faced [[Jerusalem stone]].{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}

